Gluten Free Carrot Cake

3 c blanched almond flour + more for pan
1/4 c grapeseed oil + more for pan
1 tbsp cinnamon
2 tsp sea salt
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp nutmeg
1/2 c agave nectar
5 large eggs
3 c grated carrots
1 c raisins
1 c walnuts, coarsely chopped

Preheat oven to 325F. Grease 9" diameter springform pan with oil; dust well with flour. In large bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, and nutmeg. Set aside. In medium bowl, whisk together oil, agave, and eggs, then pour into flour mixture. Whisk together until thoroughly combined. Fold in carrots, raisins, and walnuts. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 35-40 min, until tester inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool cake in pan for at least 1 hr. 

Frosting:
2 c heavy cream
2 tbsp agave nectar or honey
1 tbsp vanilla

In deep cold bowl, whip cream, agave, and vanilla until peaks form


**Can easily turn this recipe into cupcakes - divide batter amongst 12 paper lined cups, bake 35 min.
